## Analysis and Assembly Instructions

**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

*   **Block Count & Layers:** The target image displays two structures. The first structure consists of 10 blocks across 4 layers. The second structure consists of 10 blocks across 5 layers.
*   **Spatial Relationships:**
    *   **Structure 1:** The base layer consists of two red arch blocks (index 2). A yellow rectangular block (index 10) sits on top of the arches. On top of the yellow block are two red rectangular blocks (index 1), one on each side. Two orange triangle blocks (index 15) are at the top, forming a roof.
    *   **Structure 2:** The base is made of a green rectangular block (index 7). On top is an orange cylinder block (index 11). Above that is a yellow rectangular block (index 10), with two green rectangular blocks (index 8) on its sides, forming a square frame around a hole. Inside the hole sits an orange triangle block (index 15). On top of the square frame sits a green rectangular block (index 9). And finally, a blue block (index 6) rests at the top.
